link/streaming/examples/statemachine/kafka/EventDeSerializationSchema.java. This example does NOT directly wrap Kafka's Deserializer interface, but rather demonstrates how to implement Flink's DeserializationSchema for use with Kafka sources.\n\nKey Integration Points:\nWhile the provided repository dumps do not include the flink-connector-kafka module (which would contain KafkaRecordDeserializationSchema), the architecture shows that Flink provides its own DeserializationSchema abstraction that wraps Kafka's byte serialization model. Flink's DeserializationSchema operates on raw byte arrays (similar to Kafka's Deserializer) but extends Flink's type information and metrics systems. The EventDeSerializationSchema example demonstrates how to implement custom deserialization logic for Kafka-sourced data within Flink's framework.\n\nThe serialization boundary is conceptually bridged through:\n- Kafka's raw byte serialization/deserialization (Deserializer/Serializer interfaces)\n- Flink's abstraction layer (DeserializationSchema interface) that wraps byte-level operations\n- Implementation classes like EventDeSerializationSchema that provide concrete serialization logic for specific data types"
